The article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House, discussing the continuation of the national emergency with respect to the situation in or in relation to the Democratic Republic of the Congo. The letter states that the situation in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, characterized by widespread violence and atrocities, continues to pose a threat to regional stability and the foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, Obama has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13413.